      <div align="Left">
<!---------------------------->
<table cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Recommended Level<br>for starting quest:</b></td><td valign="bottom"> 61<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting zone:</b></td><td valign="top"> Plane of Knowledge<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Additional zones:</b></td><td valign="top"> All Planes of Power<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting NPC:</b></td><td valign="top"> Reaver Nydlil<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Reward:</b></td><td valign="top"> Level 61-65 spells<br><br></td></tr>
</table>

Find Reaver Nydlil in the deepest depths of the Library of Myrist (the great library) in the Plane of Knowledge.  To find the Reaver, go down the stairwell in the NE corner of the bottom floor and continue down the nearest stairwell in the first basement to get to the second basement that contains Reavers (if you see Heretics, you're on the wrong side).<br>
<br>
You say, 'Hail, Reaver Nydlil' <br>
<br>
Reaver Nydlil 's voice spills forth in a piercing hiss, the pitch high and accented in the tones of the Iksarian Empire of old, 'Welcome to New Tanaan, and stand before us as enemies not, but as equals. Your mind should be open to us, for we wish only to guide you where we have been led in our years beyond Norrath. If you a knight of the shadows, then perhaps I may be of service in guiding you further to power. The adepts of New Tanaan, the scholars, have come forward and penned spells of our former lives in memory. We wish to share this knowledge with you without bias or judgment. There is more beyond the mortal limits of magic that I can aid you to attain should you wield the blade of the shadow. If you happen across a seemingly mundane arcane item of incorporeal material, do not discard it. Return it to me and I shall carve for you from its essence a most powerful spell conceived in the divine realms of pure magic.'<br>
<br>
What Nydlil wants are the various parchments that drop in the Planes.<br>
Ethereal Parchments are good for level 61 and 62 spells<br>
Spectral Parchments are good for level 63 and 64 spells<br>
Shadowy Parchments will get you level 65 spells<Br>
<br>
The parchments usually drop off named creatures in the various planes, the higher parchments are obviously from much harder creatures.<br>
<br>
The spells you can get are:<br>
Spell: Aura of Darkness<br>
Spell: Aura of Hate<br>
Spell: Aura of Pain<br>
Spell: Blood of Hate<br>
Spell: Cloak of Luclin<br>
Spell: Deny Undead<br>
Spell: Festering Darkness<br>
Spell: Pact of Hate<br>
Spell: Shroud of Chaos<br>
Spell: Spear of Decay<br>
Spell: Terror of Thule<br>
Spell: Touch of Innoruuk<br>
Spell: Touch of Volatis<br>
Spell: Voice of Thule<br>
Spell: Zevfeer's Bite<br>

